label.value: DNA sequence data

definition.value: A sequence data item that is about the primary structure of DNA

label.value: obsolete cell lysate MHC competitive binding assay using radioactivity detection

definition.value: competitive inhibition of binding assay measuring MHC ligand binding by radioactivity detection using MHC derived from a cell lysate

label.value: assigning gene property based on phenotypic assessment

definition.value: Interpreting data from assays that evaluate the qualities or dispositions inhering in an organism or organism part and comparing it to data from other organisms that have a defined genetic difference, and assigning a property to the product of the targeted gene as a result.

label.value: obsolete purified MHC binding constant determination assay

definition.value: An assay that measures the affinity of a ligand to a purified MHC complex preparation and that quantifies the affinity with a binding constant.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific intracellular cytokine staining (ICS) IL-22 production by T cells

definition.value: A cytometric bead array assay that detects interleukin-22 production by T cells.

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific vascular endothelial growth factor production by T cells

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay that detects vascular endothelial growth factor production by T cells.

label.value: assay measuring binding of a cell-lysate-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A qualitative binding assay that detects the binding of a cell-lysate-MHC molecule with a ligand.

label.value: material transport service

definition.value: A service in which a service provider facilitates the transport of some material entity to a specified destination for the service consumer.

label.value: equilibrium dissociation constant (KD) approximated by EC50

definition.value: A measurement of an EC50 value under specific assay conditions approximates KD, namely the binding reaction is at an equilibrium,  and the concentration of the receptor must be much less than the KD for the ligand.

label.value: obsolete cell bound MHC direct binding assay

definition.value: direct binding assay measuring MHC ligand binding using MHC derived from a cell

label.value: half life of binding datum

definition.value: A half life datum of the time it takes for 50% of bound complexes in an ensemble to disassociate in absence of re-association.

label.value: phage display binding assay measuring binding of a purified-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A phage display binding assay that detects direct binding of a purified-MHC molecule with a ligand.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-7 production by T cells

definition.value: A cytometric bead array assay that detects interleukin-7 production by T cells.

label.value: radioactivity detection assay measuring half life to determine direct binding of a purified-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A radioactivity detection assay that measures half life to detect the direct binding of a purified-MHC molecule with a ligand.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-7 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-7 production by T cells.

label.value: binding

definition.value: The process of material entities forming complexes.

label.value: intracellular cytokine staining assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-17A production by T cells

definition.value: A flow cytometry assay that detects interleukin-17A production by T cells.

label.value: fluorescence detection assay measuring direct binding of a purified-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A fluorescence detection assay that detects direct binding of a purified-MHC molecule with a ligand.

label.value: direct binding assay

definition.value: A binding assay that measures the formation or disassociation of a complex of 2 material entities directly without use of a competitve ligand.

label.value: fluorescence detection assay measuring half maximal effective concentration [EC50] to determine direct binding of a purified-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A fluorescence detection assay that measures half maximal effective concentration (EC50) to detect direct binding of a purified-MHC molecule with a ligand.

label.value: competitive inhibition of binding assay

definition.value: A binding assay that detects the inhibition of binding between 2 material entities known to form a complex by the addition of a third material entity of interest. Inhibition of binding between the 2 materials reflects binding by the third material.

label.value: fluorescence detection assay measuring competitive binding of a cell-bound-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A fluorescence detection assay that detects loss of binding of a known reference ligand to cell-bound-MHC due to competition by the ligand under investigation.

label.value: X-ray crystallography assay determining the 3D structure of a MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A X-ray crystallography 3D molecular structure determination assay that characterizes the 3-dimensional molecular structure of a MHC:ligand complex.

label.value: PDB file chain

definition.value: A 3D structural organization datum that is part of a PDB file and has a specific chain identifier that identifies the entire information on a subset of the material entities.

label.value: cell bound MHC competitive binding assay measuring half maximal inhibitory concentration [IC50] of a MHC:ligand complex using T cell epitope recognition

definition.value: A cell bound MHC ligand binding half maximal inhibitory concentration (IC50) determination assay that uses a T cell epitope recognition assay to measure ligand binding.

label.value: data maintenance service

definition.value: A maintenance service in which a service provider actively manages or maintains data or a database for the service consumer.  Maintenance of the data is performed to maintain its integrity or enhance its quality or utility for the consumer, but new data is not generated as a result of the maintenance.

label.value: radioactivity detection assay measuring competitive binding of a cell-bound-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A radioactivity detection assay that detects loss of binding of a known reference ligand to cell-bound-MHC due to competition by the ligand under investigation.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific granulocyte colony stimulating factor production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects granulocyte colony stimulating factor production by T cells.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific intracellular cytokine staining (ICS) IL-21 production by T cells

definition.value: A cytometric bead array assay that detects interleukin-21 production by T cells.

label.value: radioactivity detection assay measuring direct binding of a cell-bound-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A radioactivity detection assay that detects direct binding of a cell-bound-MHC molecule with a ligand.

label.value: binding off rate measurement datum (koff)

definition.value: A rate measurement datum of how quickly bound complexes disassociate

label.value: fluorescence detection assay measuring 50% dissociation of binding temperature [Tm] of a purified-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A fluorescence detection assay that measures the 50% dissociation of binding temperature of a purified-MHC molecule with a ligand.

label.value: binding on rate measurement datum (kon)

definition.value: A rate measurement datum of how quickly bound complexes form

label.value: fluorescence detection assay measuring direct binding of a cell-bound-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A fluorescence detection assay that detects direct binding of a cell-bound-MHC molecule with a ligand.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific tumor necrosis factor (ligand) superfamily member 11 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific tumor necrosis factor (ligand) superfamily member 11 production by T cells that detects tumor necrosis factor production.

label.value: radioactivity detection assay measuring direct binding of a purified-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A radioactivity detection assay that detects direct binding of a purified-MHC molecule with a ligand.

label.value: intracellular cytokine staining assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-8 production by T cells

definition.value: A flow cytometry assay that detects interleukin-8 production by T cells.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific intracellular cytokine staining (ICS) IL-23 production by T cells

definition.value: A cytometric bead array assay that detects interleukin-23 production by T cells.

label.value: obsolete purified MHC direct binding assay

definition.value: direct binding assay measuring MHC ligand binding using MHC derived from a purified MHC molecule preparation

label.value: epitope specific vascular endothelial growth factor production by T cells

definition.value: A process of vascular endothelial growth factor production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: fluorescence detection assay measuring half maximal inhibitory concentration [IC50] to determine competitive binding of a purified-MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A fluorescence detection assay that measures half maximal inhibitory concentration (IC50) to detect the loss of binding of a known reference ligand to purified-MHC due to competition by the ligand under investigation.

label.value: GenBank ID

definition.value: A CRID symbol uniquely indentifies the submitted GeneBank sequence record.

label.value: investigation description

definition.value: A textual entity that describes an investigation.

label.value: specimen identifier

definition.value: A CRID symbol denotes a specimen and used to distinguish one specimen from another in an investigation.

label.value: PubMed ID

definition.value: A CRID symbol that is sufficient to look up a citation from the PubMed, a literature database of life sciences and biomedical information.

label.value: average depth of sequence coverage

definition.value: An average value of the depth of sequence coverage based both on external (e.g. Cot-based size estimates) and internal (average coverage in the assembly) measures of genome size.

label.value: specimen collection time measurement datum

definition.value: A time measurement datum that is the measure of the time when the specimens are collected.

label.value: latitude coordinate measurement datum

definition.value: A measurement datum that is the measure of the latitude coordinate of a site.

label.value: longitude coordinate measurement datum

definition.value: A measurement datum that is the measure of the longitude coordinate of a site.

label.value: investigation title

definition.value: A textual entity that denotes an investigation.
